node.text:
Thanks so much to everyone who joined our live yesterday with my good friend & life coach @noradekeyser for the @mentalhealthcoalition’s 1-2-1 Series. We talked all things mental health, the toxic culture of comparison, and were even joined by the amazing @bbarthur, Founder + CEO of @the.difference.co.
This series was inspired by the notion that every 1 needs to talk 2 some 1, and I hope this conversation helps give some of y’all the courage to reach out to someone for support and have these open, stigma free conversations around mental health. Having someone to talk to is so important. Just remember that you're not alone. ❤️ #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text: A September to Remember! Leyon and I are both celebrating our birthdays this September, and there is no better gift than the gift of health. 2020 has been a hard year with many setbacks...but we are going to reclaim our year and the health of our mind, body, and soul! Check out all the info on @leyon to find out how you can get the on demand workouts and be a part of this journey! I’m in it with you!  Wohooo! Let’s do it fam! 💪🏼

node.text:
Today feels really symbolic for me. As I get ready to move into a new home, I realize that I am starting a new chapter and closing another. (Which is a big deal because I’m usually rushing to the next chapter before I finish the one before!) 
 
I took a trip down memory lane this morning, looking at footage and personal journals from The Bachelor and The Bachelorette, and couldn’t help but feel a little proud of how much I’ve evolved since then. I recorded this video after one of the first few episodes aired of The Bachelor (probably in between the time I couldn’t make a toast and roared [rawr!] on camera) in January 2019! Oh sweet baby Han didn’t know then it was just the start of all the crazy mess she’d get into! I’ve had lots of highs and a lot of lows, and although I would prefer some things to have gone differently, I wouldn’t change a single thing. I’m thankful for every single one of my experiences and the subsequent moments of growth, and of course, I’m thankful for all of you! Tough times don’t feel so rough when you have some pretty great friends on the internet rooting for ya along the way!  
 
Cheers, to new beginnings y’all! 💛

node.text: It’s #NationalRelaxationDay and I wanted to share one of the ways I like to unwind. It’s so important to take some time out of the week to do something for YOU. Sometimes all you need is a paint brush and some good food. 🌮What are some things you do to unwind and relax?
